advanced-guides/introduction.title: Introduction
advanced-guides/introduction.description: Throughout Trackpac we offer a range of ways to use our platform. In this section we'll talk about some advanced options for our platform and how to use them.

api-guides/authenticating.title: Authenticating with the Trackpac API
api-guides/authenticating.description: This guide outlines two methods to authenticate your API requests with Trackpac: retrieving the Auth0 bearer token from local storage or obtaining the token via a curl request.

api-guides/importing-into-postman.title: Importing Trackpac API into Postman
api-guides/importing-into-postman.description: This guide will walk you through the process of importing Trackpac's OpenAPI specification into Postman. This allows you to easily test and explore Trackpac's API endpoints.

api-guides/index.title: Introduction
api-guides/index.description: Welcome to the Trackpac API Guides section! The Trackpac API allows you to interact programmatically with our IoT dashboard, offering capabilities like alerts, actions, forwarders, and more. Whether you're an administrator, developer, or end-user, this guide aims to provide you with comprehensive instructions and examples to get you up to speed.

api-guides/location-engine.title: Location Engine API Resolution
api-guides/location-engine.description: Our Location engine offers two modes of resolution, LoRaWAN and WIFI.

device-guides/browan-tabs-object-locator.title: Browan Tabs TBOL100
device-guides/browan-tabs-object-locator.description: Getting started with a Browan tabs object locator couldnt be easier. Follow our step-by-step guide below to get started.

device-guides/index.title: Intro
device-guides/index.description: This section is full of device-specific guides, showing you the process from arrival right through to monitoring them and adding alerts.

getting-started/add-a-base.title: Add a Base
getting-started/add-a-base.description: If your device is a sticker Tracker (Nanothings Nanotag or RAKwireless 2270 Sticker Tracker) you can add bases for your stickers.

getting-started/add-a-contact.title: Add a Contact
getting-started/add-a-contact.description: Follow these simple steps to add a new contact to your account for receiving alerts or notifications.

getting-started/add-a-device.title: Add a Device
getting-started/add-a-device.description: Once you have created an account and logged in, the next step is adding a device for monitoring.

getting-started/add-a-geofence.title: Add a Geofence
getting-started/add-a-geofence.description: If your device is an asset tracker, you can add a geofence to get alerts when a tracker enters or exits and area.

getting-started/add-an-action.title: Add an Action
getting-started/add-an-action.description: Use this guide to set up a new action that triggers alerts or forwards data based on various conditions.

getting-started/index.title: Sign up
getting-started/index.description: Welcome to our platform! This guide will walk you through the essential steps to get you up and running.

getting-started/manage-organisations.title: Organisations
getting-started/manage-organisations.description: The Organisations feature provides a structured way to manage multiple devices based on varying criteria such as projects, customer groups, or locations. This allows for easier management of contacts, actions, and geofences, while also permitting you to grant access to multiple members.

getting-started/managing-a-device.title: Managing a Device
getting-started/managing-a-device.description: Our platform aims to provide an intuitive user experience while accommodating a variety of device types, each with unique features and capabilities. Whether you're monitoring a temperature sensor or a tracking device, the necessary data is displayed in an organized and customizable manner.
